notesStmt.note: Imperfect at the beginning and at the end. Lacunae after folios 3 and 6, and quires 17-20 are entirely lost.
Folios 270r-270v - contains doodles, magical squares, etc.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 19; written lines: 19; The unpointed Hebrew text is embodied. Has many marginal notes.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Square and semi-cursive script of 13 to 14th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Caraite Commentary on Exodus. Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2398.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 23 July 1881, folio [271v].
